A Bronx teenager was charged with murder Friday in connection with a January Brooklyn shooting. Kendu Skeen, 18, of Wakefield was arrested for killing Ahmad Perkins, 45, in a broad daylight attack in front of a Crown Heights apartment building on Jan. 31, police said. Skeen allegedly shot Perkins in the head. He was charged with murder and criminal possession of a weapon, according to the NYPD.